§<~>53<~>.<~>The<~>last<~>part<~>of<~>our<~>work<~>presents<~>itself<~>as<~>the<~>most<~>serious<~>,<~>for<~>*NL*<~>it<~>relates<~>to<~>the<~>action<~>of<~>men<~>,<~>the<~>matter<~>which<~>concerns<~>every<~>one<~>*NL*<~>directly<~>and<~>can<~>be<~>foreign<~>or<~>indifferent<~>to<~>none<~>.<~>It<~>is<~>indeed<~>so<~>*NL*<~>characteristic<~>of<~>the<~>nature<~>of<~>man<~>to<~>relate<~>everything<~>else<~>to<~>action<~>,<~>*NL*<~>that<~>in<~>every<~>systematic<~>investigation<~>he<~>will<~>always<~>treat<~>the<~>part<~>that<~>*NL*<~>has<~>to<~>do<~>with<~>action<~>as<~>the<~>result<~>or<~>outcome<~>of<~>the<~>whole<~>work<~>,<~>so<~>far<~>,<~>*NL*<~>at<~>least<~>,<~>as<~>it<~>interests<~>him<~>,<~>and<~>will<~>therefore<~>give<~>his<~>most<~>serious<~>*NL*<~>attention<~>to<~>this<~>part<~>,<~>even<~>if<~>to<~>no<~>other<~>.<~>In<~>this<~>respect<~>the<~>following<~>*NL*<~>part<~>of<~>our<~>work<~>would<~>,<~>in<~>ordinary<~>language<~>,<~>be<~>called<~>practical<~>*NL*<~>philosophy<~>,<~>in<~>opposition<~>to<~>the<~>theoretical<~>,<~>which<~>has<~>occupied<~>us<~>*NL*<~>hitherto<~>.<~>But<~>,<~>in<~>my<~>opinion<~>,<~>all<~>philosophy<~>is<~>theoretical<~>,<~>because<~>it<~>is<~>*NL*<~>essential<~>to<~>it<~>that<~>it<~>should<~>retain<~>a<~>purely<~>contemplative<~>attitude<~>,<~>and<~>*NL*<~>should<~>investigate<~>,<~>not<~>prescribe<~>.<~>To<~>become<~>,<~>on<~>the<~>contrary<~>,<~>practical<~>,<~>*NL*<~>to<~>guide<~>conduct<~>,<~>to<~>transform<~>character<~>,<~>are<~>old<~>claims<~>,<~>which<~>with<~>*NL*<~>fuller<~>insight<~>it<~>ought<~>finally<~>to<~>give<~>up<~>.<~>For<~>here<~>,<~>where<~>the<~>worth<~>or<~>*NL*<~>worthlessness<~>of<~>an<~>existence<~>,<~>where<~>salvation<~>or<~>damnation<~>are<~>in<~>*NL*<~>question<~>,<~>the<~>dead<~>conceptions<~>of<~>philosophy<~>do<~>not<~>decide<~>the<~>matter<~>,<~>but<~>*NL*<~>the<~>inmost<~>nature<~>of<~>man<~>himself<~>,<~>the<~>Dæmon<~>that<~>guides<~>him<~>and<~>that<~>has<~>*NL*<~>not<~>chosen<~>him<~>,<~>but<~>been<~>chosen<~>by<~>him<~>,<~>as<~>Plato<~>would<~>say<~>;<~>his<~>*NL*<~>intelligible<~>character<~>,<~>as<~>Kant<~>expresses<~>himself<~>.<~>Virtue<~>can<~>not<~>be<~>taught<~>*NL*<~>any<~>more<~>than<~>genius<~>;<~>indeed<~>,<~>for<~>it<~>the<~>concept<~>is<~>just<~>as<~>unfruitful<~>as<~>*NL*<~>it<~>is<~>in<~>art<~>,<~>and<~>in<~>both<~>cases<~>can<~>only<~>be<~>used<~>as<~>an<~>instrument<~>.<~>It<~>*NL*<~>would<~>,<~>therefore<~>,<~>be<~>just<~>as<~>absurd<~>to<~>expect<~>that<~>our<~>moral<~>systems<~>and<~>*NL*<~>ethics<~>will<~>produce<~>virtuous<~>,<~>noble<~>,<~>and<~>holy<~>men<~>,<~>as<~>that<~>our<~>æsthetics<~>*NL*<~>will<~>produce<~>poets<~>,<~>painters<~>,<~>and<~>musicians<~>.<~>*NL*<~>*NL*<~>Philosophy<~>can<~>never<~>do<~>more<~>than<~>interpret<~>and<~>explain<~>what<~>is<~>given<~>.<~>It<~>*NL*<~>can<~>only<~>bring<~>to<~>distinct<~>abstract<~>knowledge<~>of<~>the<~>reason<~>the<~>nature<~>of<~>*NL*<~>the<~>world<~>which<~>in<~>the<~>concrete<~>,<~>that<~>is<~>,<~>as<~>feeling<~>,<~>expresses<~>itself<~>*NL*<~>comprehensibly<~>to<~>every<~>one<~>.<~>This<~>,<~>however<~>,<~>it<~>does<~>in<~>every<~>possible<~>*NL*<~>reference<~>and<~>from<~>every<~>point<~>of<~>view<~>.<~>Now<~>,<~>as<~>this<~>attempt<~>has<~>been<~>made<~>*NL*<~>from<~>other<~>points<~>of<~>view<~>in<~>the<~>three<~>preceding<~>books<~>with<~>the<~>generality<~>*NL*<~>that<~>is<~>proper<~>to<~>philosophy<~>,<~>in<~>this<~>book<~>the<~>action<~>of<~>men<~>will<~>be<~>*NL*<~>considered<~>in<~>the<~>same<~>way<~>;<~>and<~>this<~>side<~>of<~>the<~>world<~>might<~>,<~>indeed<~>,<~>be<~>*NL*<~>considered<~>the<~>most<~>important<~>of<~>all<~>,<~>not<~>only<~>subjectively<~>,<~>as<~>I<~>remarked<~>*NL*<~>above<~>,<~>but<~>also<~>objectively<~>.<~>In<~>considering<~>it<~>I<~>shall<~>faithfully<~>adhere<~>*NL*<~>to<~>the<~>method<~>I<~>have<~>hitherto<~>followed<~>,<~>and<~>shall<~>support<~>myself<~>by<~>*NL*<~>presupposing<~>all<~>that<~>has<~>already<~>been<~>advanced<~>.<~>There<~